South Africa July Monthly Budget Balance Returns to Deficit, Treasury Says

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-08-30T12:04:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/south-africa-july-monthly-budget-balance-returns-to-deficit-treasury-says.html
South Africa  posted a budget deficit
of 44.1 billion rand ($6.2 billion) in July, compared with a
surplus of 12.6 billion rand in June, the National Treasury
said.  Tax revenue fell 4.7 percent to 41.2 billion rand from a
year earlier, while expenditure rose 14 percent to 85.2 billion
rand, the Pretoria-based Treasury said on its website today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Gordon Bell  at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  